article.headline: Williams helps Tarleton State fend off UT Arlington 80-78
article.description: — Lue Williams scored 22 points to help Tarleton State hold off UT Arlington 80-78 on Thursday night for its sixth straight victory.
article.linkText: Williams helps Tarleton State fend off UT Arlington 80-78
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- — Lue Williams scored 22 points to help Tarleton State hold off UT Arlington 80-78 on Thursday night for its sixth straight victory. Williams was 8-of-11 shooting, including 2 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 5 from the foul line for the Texans (18-7, 11-3 Western Athletic Conference). Jakorie Smith scored 18 points and grabbed five rebounds. Kiandre Gaddy scored 12. DaJuan Gordon led the Mavericks (12-13, 7-7) with 20 points and 13 rebounds. Makaih Williams added 16 points and Phillip Russell scored 12. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
